  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF AGGRESSIVE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;60</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;3 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;27 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;27 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>The warrior will do more damage with every blow landed but will also take more damage as well. This discipline lasts for 3 minutes and has a base reuse time of 27 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IMP</span><b>, By Imp</b><br><br>What you aren't looking at is the exponential factor of this dicipline.  The point is to do exponential damage. It's not 'oh I will do x more damage per hit, but my damage per hit will increase By x, so if I do 2 damage the first hit I would do 4 the next hit then 8 the next hit, That adds up extremely fast, and likewise you take (rumor0 exponential damage. I see it as a last ditch effort to do so much damage. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>HMM....</span><b>, By Commenter</b><br><br>I assume that you are using Nagafen as a theoretical encounter, since lvl 60's are too high to attack him.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>A COMMENT.</span><b>, By Just</b><br><br>I think you guys aren't thinking of tactics here, lets see a group has 6 people, a nagafen group has 20. Its not like you are going to be the target all of the time, unless of course you are already doing the most damage, so lets say you are at naga, hes beeting on fighter # 1, not you # 2, so you figure hell, im not getting hit, lets dish out some extra beats. so now your hitting for extra damage , naga is hitting #1, and youre happy, when naga switches to you , #1 can use his special to get its attention again, mean while , fighters 3 4 5 6 7 can all be doing this too, I dont think you guys are thinking of the tactical advantages here, this game is certainly not ment to be one on one, so why are you looking at it that way??<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>AWESOME SKILL</span><b>, By Loredon icereaver</b><br><br>Use this and mighty strike or fell strike and your a damage machine combine this also with an enchanter's rune spell it should lessen the damage you take considerably and therefor nix the advantage of monsters hitting harder another thing is that with this new colbalt stuff which is like a blessing with 25ac a piece and not to mention we will probably be around oh 2900 hp base by that time itll be nice to experiment with though<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
